The paper deals with the problem of super-resolution, which is a common topic in image processing and computer vision (cs.CV). However, the paper focuses on the mathematical formulation of the problem and the use of convex optimization techniques to solve it, which suggests a strong connection to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the stability of the proposed method, which is a common concern in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations and experiments, which suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
